    "## Comparing BoW and TF-IDF\n",
    "\n",
    "| Property | Bag of Words | TF-IDF |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Representation | Raw counts | Weighted counts |\n",
    "| Common word handling | Counts them equally | Penalizes common words |\n",
    "| Unique word emphasis | None | Boosts discriminating terms |\n",
    "| Interpretability | High | High |\n",
    "| Best for | Baselines, frequency tasks | Classification, similarity |\n",
    "\n",
    "Both representations produce **sparse, fixed-length vectors** — they are the foundation before learning dense embeddings.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sentiment Analysis with a PyTorch MLP\n",
    "\n",
    "## From Features to Neural Classification\n",
    "\n",
    "Once text is represented as TF-IDF vectors, we can feed those vectors directly into a neural network.\n",
    "This bridges **classical NLP feature engineering** and **deep learning**.\n",
    "\n",
    "The architecture is a simple **Multi-Layer Perceptron (MLP)**:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\hat{y} = \\text{softmax}(W_2 \\cdot \\text{ReLU}(W_1 x + b_1) + b_2)\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where $x$ is the TF-IDF vector for a document.\n",
    "\n",
    "## TextMLP in PyTorch"
