    "## From Classical NLP to Deep Learning\n",
    "\n",
    "| Era | Representation | Model | Strength |\n",
    "|---|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Classical | BoW / TF-IDF | Naïve Bayes, SVM | Fast, interpretable |\n",
    "| Transition | Word2Vec embeddings | Shallow MLP | Semantic similarity |\n",
    "| Deep Learning | Contextual embeddings | RNN, LSTM | Sequence-aware |\n",
    "| Modern | Transformer embeddings | BERT, GPT | Full-context, generative |\n",
    "\n",
    "Each row builds on the previous.\n",
    "The MLP above sits at the **transition row** — it uses classical features (TF-IDF) but learns nonlinear patterns through a neural network.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Strengths and Limitations of BoW\n",
    "\n",
    "## Strengths\n",
    "- Simple  \n",
    "- Fast  \n",
    "- Effective for short, structured text  \n",
    "\n",
    "## Limitations\n",
    "- Ignores order and meaning  \n",
    "- Sparse representations  \n",
    "- Vocabulary explosion  \n",
    "\n",
